{"TopicId":185186,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Random Spinning with no SAS","CreatedByName":"Rocketthrust","CreatedById":152032,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-06T02:20:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Rocketthrust","CreatedById":152032,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-06T02:20:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve noticed this on many of my crafts that when there is no \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on board the ship spins faster and faster.\u00A0 I\u0027ve also turned off reaction wheels and it keeps increasing rotation.\u00A0 I run 1.7.1 on windows 10 using steam.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-06T02:57:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNullify your trim.\u00A0\u00A0 Alt/ctrl-x\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 I forget what it is exactly.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoved to Gameplay Questions, as I don\u0027t think this is a tech support issue.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-06T04:43:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this happening in the atmosphere, or in space?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocketthrust","CreatedById":152032,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-06T19:01:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223613109\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185186\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221559796188\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this happening in the atmosphere, or in space?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, but the atmosphere limits it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Goody1981","CreatedById":153740,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-07T01:53:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had this issue after the update as well. I cancelled the trim but it did nothing - I would still keep rolling (there was no trim set anyway). I verified my install (through GOG) and I also increased the deadzones of my joystick, and recalibrated it. That\u0027s a terrible science experiment cos I changed three things before checking - but one of them worked! Hope that is somewhat helpful \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-07T01:53:57Z\u0022 title=\u002206/07/2019 01:53  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 7, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Goody1981\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-07T17:24:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMake sure your joystick is centered.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}